<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Washington Naval Arms Conference resulted in:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Increased naval competition</option>
            <option letter="b">Naval arms limitations among major powers</option>
            <option letter="c">Military alliance formation</option>
            <option letter="d">Arms race acceleration</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Washington Naval Arms Conference (1921-1922) produced the Five-Power Treaty, establishing a 5:5:3:1.75:1.75 ratio of naval strength between the United States, Britain, Japan, France, and Italy. This agreement successfully limited naval armaments among major powers, reduced military spending, and represented a significant diplomatic effort to prevent a naval arms race in the post-World War I era.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
